      • addType

        public Type addType(Type type)
        Adds the specified element to this set if it is not already present (optional operation) and returns it. More formally, adds the specified element e to this set if the set contains no element e2 such that (e==null ? e2==null : e.equals(e2)). If this set already contains the element, the call leaves the set unchanged and returns the existing element. In combination with the restriction on constructors, this ensures that sets never contain duplicate elements.
        Parameters:
        type - - the element that needs to be added
        Returns:
        The same element if it's a new one or the existing element if this set contains the specified element.

      • typeEnforceTaxonomyStructure

        public java.lang.String typeEnforceTaxonomyStructure(java.lang.String rootTypeID,
                                                     TypeAutomaton typeAutomaton,
                                                     AtomMapping mappings)
        Generating the mandatory usage of a subtypes in case of the parent type being used, with respect to the Type Taxonomy. The rule starts from the @rootType and it's valid in each state of @typeAutomaton. @emptyType denotes the type that is being used if the state has no type.
        Parameters:
        rootTypeID - - represent the ID of the root type in the type taxonomy
        emptyTypeID - - represent the ID of the empty type in the type taxonomy
        typeAutomaton - - type automaton
        mappings - - mapping function
        Returns:
        String representation of constraints enforcing taxonomy classifications
